				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "RK6lCCb8SNioCeI0yRsAJA=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Glamorous Toolkit is a live environment. Generating code ([[Moldable Chat: Generating code]]) or documentation ([[Moldable Chat: Changing Lepiter pages]]) is useful, but to leverage the environment’s full potential beyond what is possible elsewhere, we should get the LLM to work with objects."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [
						{
							"__type" : "pharoSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-04T23:29:06.851715+01:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T13:56:52.349678+01:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "quo0JQBuSU2JYTc6x0RqeQ=="
							},
							"code" : "c := GtL gt\n\tsendMarkdown: 'Produce a script that builds an 16x16 element with icon that shows a simple home. Take as blueprint for the script, the icon defined in {{gtMethod:BrGlamorousVectorIcons class>>chat}} which uses {{gtClass:BlPolygonGeometry}}. Execute the code. Evaluate the result by viewing the Live view of the resulting object. Give a grade of the result.'"
						},
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T13:58:10.2729+01:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:20:28.970019+01:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "8lpSRidvRJqARpzGsX6PwQ=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "To check the Live view of the resulting element, it needs a means to pass the reference from resulting from the code execution tool to the tool that gets the view. This is achieved through an object storage (see {{gtMethod:GtLChat>>#objectStorage}}) that associates ids to objects and stores them in a chat. Tools like  {{gtClass:GtLMagritteToolForSmalltalkCodeEvaluation}} use this mechanism to store results, and other tools such as {{gtClass:GtLToolForObjectView}} can interpret ids passed as arguments."
						},
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T14:50:49.986495+01:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:20:44.498504+01:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "1PxInidLQueMxxT0E8czKA=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "If you want to explore this use case further, try this:"
						},
						{
							"__type" : "pharoSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T13:55:50.250253+01:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T13:56:08.106243+01:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "8o0vv99UT6a0NaTZwy6tzA=="
							},
							"code" : "c sendMarkdown: 'Improve it to get a higher grade.'"
						}
					]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T13:02:32.691154+01:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:19:38.253079+01:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "wHemmL7IQwWnMNOAc1deMg=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Let's start with a basic case in which we ask the LLM to produce a script that builds an icon. We also ask it to run the script and then evaluate the result by looking at the view:"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T21:59:28.548556+01:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:20:57.508682+01:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "ilPJ37bfRM2NVgF4/KSD5g=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Inspecting the result of a script and viewing it is equivalent to working in a playground and an inspector. To complete the picture and allow the LLM to reach and inspect arbitrary objects, we also need the equivalent of a contextual playground. To this end, we need to be able to bind objects to variables in a script."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [
						{
							"__type" : "pharoSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-04T23:34:33.488185+01:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:01:54.150115+01:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "Xh5Iq01OQGSNJUJsK1hiXA=="
							},
							"code" : "GtL gt\r\tsendMarkdown: 'Execute {{gtMethod:BlGridLayoutExamples>>#exampleCellSpacingHorizontal1}}. What are the exact bounds of the two blue squares?'"
						},
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:02:05.969467+01:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:21:31.09693+01:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "NFDk+UHbRxawq0IxKGjLYg=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "The example method produces an element. To obtain details about that element, the LLM has to execute a script with a variable bound to the element. The example method tool stores the resulting object in the object storage, and the LLM has the option of binding a name to an ID as an argument in {{gtMethod:GtLMagritteToolForSmalltalkCodeEvaluation>>#bindingsDescription}}. Inspect the Smalltalk execution message in the chat above to see this in action."
						}
					]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:01:12.284947+01:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:21:08.322021+01:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "doZBE3LNSJS1xSSgcKKUjw=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "The case below exemplifies this idea:"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:08:12.509234+01:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:21:48.804866+01:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "lGEOW/N0TCqtpIHF6sPJ8g=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "The above scenario is equivalent to inspecting the result of an example method and running a script in a contextual playground on that result. Sometimes, however, we want to start the conversation from an existing object in the image."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [
						{
							"__type" : "pharoSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-04T23:34:38.415362+01:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:11:49.002236+01:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "cEb9eKYsRyOJ5q32RRjdIg=="
							},
							"code" : "container := BrVerticalPane new matchParent; background: Color paleOrange.\rc := GtL gt.\rc objectStorage addNewObject: container.\rc sendMarkdown: 'You have an input object in the object storage. Execute {{gtMethod:BlGridLayoutExamples>>#exampleCellSpacingHorizontal1}}. Add the result to the original input object' "
						},
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:10:05.200389+01:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-03-13T22:22:23.092671+01:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "z1KIG69QQA26RVUUpl/BSA=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "In this example, the LLM must find the ID of the input object. It can do that with {{gtClass:GtLToolForObjectStorageList}}. It can then run the example to get another object’s ID, and eventually execute a script that relies on both IDs."
						},
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
